DEFINITIONS (ยง 14-6099)
(a) Annual Income includes, but is not limited to, the following:
(1) The full amount, before any payroll deduction, of wages and salaries,vertime pay, commissions, fees, tips, and bonuses, and other compensation forersonal services;
(2) The net income from operation of a business or profession. Expendituresor business expansion or amortization of capital indebtedness shall not be useds deductions in determining net income. An allowance for depreciation ofssets used in a business or profession may be deducted, based on straight lineepreciation, as provided in Internal Revenue Service regulations. Anyithdrawal of cash or assets from the operation of a business or profession wille included in income, except to the extent the withdrawal is reimbursement ofash or assets invested in the operation by the family;
(3) Interest, dividends, and other net income of any kind from real or personalroperty greater than $1,000 per year. Expenditures for amortization of capitalndebtedness shall be used as deduction in determining net income. All allowanceor depreciation is permitted only as authorized in paragraph (a)(2) of thisefinition. Net income from assets will be included in Annual Income for theurposes of this title if net income from assets exceeds $1,000.
Notwithstanding this threshold, all assets with a value greater than $15,000ust be reported annually. Regardless of the value of the assets, imputedncome from assets will not be included in Annual Income.
